Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["6. Residues at the Poles", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"40c17664-9ed5-405d-86ce-1ef75b2d79fa"],

Cell["\<\
Each component of the Green\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tensor now has simple poles at \
\[Xi]1 = \[PlusMinus]\[Nu]L (P-wave poles) and \[Xi]1 = \[PlusMinus]\[Nu]T \
(S-wave poles).

The physical interpretation: \[Nu]L and \[Nu]T are the vertical wavenumbers \
for downgoing (+) and upgoing (-) P-waves and S-waves respectively. Which \
poles are enclosed depends on the sign of the depth separation and the chosen \
contour closure (upper or lower half-plane).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4800d7f1-7dbc-41f9-b341-27a6c8ce4426"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* P-wave poles: \[Xi]1 = \[PlusMinus]\[Nu]L *)
resLp = Simplify[Table[Residue[Rhat[i, k], {\[Xi]1, \[Nu]L}], {i, 1, 3}, {k, \
1, 3}]];
resLm = Simplify[Table[Residue[Rhat[i, k], {\[Xi]1, -\[Nu]L}], {i, 1, 3}, {k, \
1, 3}]];
Column[{Style[\"P-wave pole at \[Xi]1 = +\[Nu]L:\", Bold], MatrixForm[resLp], \
Style[\"P-wave pole at \[Xi]1 = -\[Nu]L:\", Bold], MatrixForm[resLm]}, \
Spacings -> 1]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[32]:=",ExpressionUUID->"bf1d4d53-848b-4e1f-abaa-1d29e8640429"],

